<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - WHEELS, RIMS AND TIRES - WHEEL AND WHEEL ASSEMBLIES REMOVAL
        AND INSTALLATION - DISC WHEELS (REMOVAL)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>DISC WHEELS (REMOVAL)</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Tire and Wheel</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1700112">Figure 12</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1700113">Figure 13</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1700112" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1700112" filename="../figg17/G1700112.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="392px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Disc Rear Wheel Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1700113" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1700113" filename="../figg17/G1700113.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="392px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Disc Front Wheel Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Set parking brake and block wheels not being serviced to prevent vehicle from moving.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Break all wheel nuts loose on wheel(s) being serviced.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position vehicle on floor stand(s).</para>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>A jack must never be used alone to support vehicle while under-chassis service is being
                            performed. The jack may lower and serious personal injury could result. Always support
                            vehicle with floor stands.
                        </para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If brake service is to be performed, loosen or back off brake adjustment so that the
                    drum will move freely without drag (not required with disc brakes). Refer to GROUP 04 - BRAKES in
                    the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove wheel nuts (outer nuts with dual wheels at rear) (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1700114">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1700114" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1700114" filename="../figg17/G1700114.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="232px" scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 14. Remove Outer Wheel Nuts (Ball Seat)</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove wheel from wheel studs.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">On dual wheel application, remove the inner wheel nuts and wheel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1700115">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1700115" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1700115" filename="../figg17/G1700115.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="232px" scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 15. Remove Inner Wheel Nuts (Ball Seat)</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
